      • isError

        public boolean isError()
        Indicates an error occurred during the parsing of the packet. This may indicate a bug in this software or in the XBee firmware. Absence of an error does not indicate the request was successful; you will need to inspect the status byte of the response object (if available) to determine success.

      • parse

        protected abstract void parse(IPacketParser parser)
                       throws java.io.IOException
        All subclasses must implement to parse the packet from the input stream. The subclass must parse all bytes in the packet starting after the API_ID, and up to but not including the checksum. Reading either more or less bytes that expected will result in an error.
        Parameters:
        parser -
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
